sm and the anti-capitalist and anti-globalisation movements.Key FeaturesExplores the manufacture of the self in consumer society*Suitable for readers interested in philosophy of mind, poststructuralist political theory, and connections between psychology, sociology and politics*Adds to a small but growing literature regarding the interconnection between neuropsychology and politics"  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aNeuropsychology. 0aPolitical science. 4aPolitics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z97831107804680 cprintz978074862386040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748630226?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748630226423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748630226/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK